COPS in the USA have arrested a 70-year-old gogo for assaulting a nurse on Monday, 20 June. According to kitv.com, the shocking incident happened at Kaiser Permanente Moanalua Medical Centre. It is reported that the nurse was busy with her duties when the gogo started being violent with hospital employees over the discharge of another patient. READ: ESIDIMENI: Nurses refuse to talk The Honolulu police department said the gogo was arrested at the scene and charged with assault. She was released on $500 bail (about R7 900). In a statement, the hospital said it took the safety of its staff and patients seriously. “We are cooperating fully with law enforcement authorities. We are committed to maintaining a safe environment for our patients, staff and anyone who visits a Kaiser Permanente facility,” the statement read.